## Executive Summary
HireVue is a Utah-based HR Technology company founded in 2004 that provides an enterprise-focused, AI-powered "Human Potential Intelligence" platform [What is HireVue's business model?](https://vizologi.com/business-strategy-canvas/hirevue-business-model-canvas/); [HireVue | LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/company/hirevue). Operating on a B2B SaaS model with a sales-led go-to-market strategy, the company has achieved significant traction, reaching $89 million in ARR by June 2024 and surpassing 80 million global interviews by 2026 [HireVue Revenue 2024: $89M ARR, $150M Valuation](https://getlatka.com/companies/hirevue); [About the Company Hirevue](https://www.hirevue.com/about). Backed by major investors and majority-owned by The Carlyle Group since 2019, HireVue continues to expand its capabilities through strategic acquisitions like Modern Hire and Hireguide [HireVue Announces Close of Transaction with The Carlyle Group | Carlyle](https://www.carlyle.com/media-room/news-release-archive/hirevue-announces-close-transaction-carlyle-group); [HireVue - 2026 Company Profile, Team, Funding & Competitors - Tracxn](https://tracxn.com/d/companies/hirevue/__PeMrputcdA2VOkFKx0ff0NX85_cSCaYi7B2wCL8qA6Y).

## Key Findings

### Identity & Positioning
HireVue operates in the HR Technology sector, specifically focusing on talent acquisition and video interviewing [What is HireVue's business model?](https://vizologi.com/business-strategy-canvas/hirevue-business-model-canvas/). The company targets enterprise clients across finance, healthcare, technology, retail, manufacturing, and the public sector [What Is HireVue? | Definition from TechTarget](https://www.techtarget.com/searchhrsoftware/definition/HireVue). Its core features include OnDemand video interviewing, AI-powered assessments, and automated interview scheduling [Hirevue | AI-Powered Skill Validation, Video Interviewing, Assessments and More](https://www.hirevue.com). A key differentiator is its deep I-O psychology-backed competency mapping and highly configurable automated workflows [HireVue: 2025 Technical Deep Dive into AI Hiring, Features, and Critical Compliance - Best AI HR Source](https://bestaihrsource.com/talent-acquisition/hirevue-overview-features-breakdown). 

### Financials & Traction
HireVue has raised between $93.4 million and $390 million across multiple funding rounds, with backing from notable investors like Sequoia Capital, Granite Ventures, and TCV [HireVue - 2026 Company Profile, Team, Funding & Competitors - Tracxn](https://tracxn.com/d/companies/hirevue/__PeMrputcdA2VOkFKx0ff0NX85_cSCaYi7B2wCL8qA6Y); [HireVue 2026 Company Profile: Valuation, Funding & Investors | PitchBook](https://pitchbook.com/profiles/company/47555-65). In 2019, The Carlyle Group acquired a majority stake in a deal estimated at $400 million, based on a reported EBITDA of approximately $50 million [HireVue to review exit options in 2-3 years, CEO says - ION Analytics](https://ionanalytics.com/insights/mergermarket/hirevue-to-review-exit-options-in-2-3-years-ceo-says/). The company's ARR grew from $32.1 million in 2021 to $89 million in June 2024 [HireVue Revenue 2024: $89M ARR, $150M Valuation](https://getlatka.com/companies/hirevue).

### Leadership & Strategy
The executive team is led by CEO Jeremy Friedman, CTO Alberto Silveira, and CPO Marcy Daniel [Jeremy Friedman Appointed as Hirevue CEO to Lead Next Phase of Growth | Hirevue](https://www.hirevue.com/press-release/jeremy-friedman-appointed-as-hirevue-ceo-to-lead-next-phase-of-growth); [Alberto Silveira - HireVue | LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/in/asilveira/); [Hirevue cements federal hiring leadership with latest FedRAMP milestone | Hirevue](https://www.hirevue.com/press-release/hirevue-cements-federal-hiring-leadership-with-latest-fedramp-milestone). HireVue has aggressively pursued inorganic growth, acquiring AllyO in 2020 for $50M-$100M, Modern Hire in 2023, and Hireguide in March 2026 to enhance its agentic AI capabilities [Carlyle-backed HireVue buys VC-funded AllyO for $50m to $100m | PE Hub](https://www.pehub.com/carlyle-backed-hirevue-buys-vc-funded-allyo-for-50m-to-100m/); [Modern and HireVue Transaction | William Blair](https://www.williamblair.com/News/Modern-and-HireVue-Transaction); [HireVue - 2026 Company Profile, Team, Funding & Competitors - Tracxn](https://tracxn.com/d/companies/hirevue/__PeMrputcdA2VOkFKx0ff0NX85_cSCaYi7B2wCL8qA6Y).

## Analysis / Risk Assessment
HireVue demonstrates strong enterprise market penetration, serving over 60% of the Fortune 100 and holding the unique position of being the only FedRAMP-authorized hiring solution for the public sector [Hirevue - LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/company/hirevue); [Hirevue | AI-Powered Skill Validation, Video Interviewing, Assessments and More](https://www.hirevue.com). Its sales-led motion with high starting price points ($35,000/year) indicates a solid upmarket focus [Top 5 HireVue Alternatives | Compare Features and Cons](https://www.blogs.zappyhire.com/post/top-hirevue-alternatives-compare-features-and-cons/). However, conflicting reports regarding its total customer count (1,150 vs. 25,000) and total funding ($93.4M vs. $390M) suggest some opacity or inconsistency in public data reporting [How HireVue hit $89M revenue and 25K customers in 2024.](https://getlatka.com/companies/hirevue); [HireVue 2026 Company Profile: Valuation, Funding & Investors | PitchBook](https://pitchbook.com/profiles/company/47555-65).

## Gaps and Limitations
- **Identity:** Exact HQ city, employee count, and YoY employee growth are not disclosed in the findings.
- **Pricing:** Detailed pricing tiers and the existence of a free plan are not available.
- **Customers:** No specific named customers are mentioned in the findings, only aggregate statistics (e.g., Fortune 100).
- **Signals:** No user complaints or weaknesses from review sites (G2, Capterra, Reddit) were found.
- **Team:** Some executive LinkedIn URLs are missing, and there are conflicting sources regarding the Chief People Officer and CEO identities in older or less reliable directories.

